<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><xmi:XMI xmlns:type3="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/frequency/tfidf/type.ecore" xmlns:cas="http:///uima/cas.ecore" xmlns:type4="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/metadata/type.ecore" xmlns:dependency="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/syntax/type/dependency.ecore" xmlns:type8="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/syntax/type.ecore" xmlns:type9="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/type.ecore" xmlns:type5="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/ner/type.ecore" xmlns:type6="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/segmentation/type.ecore" xmlns:tcas="http:///uima/tcas.ecore" xmlns:pathos="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/argumentation/types/pathos.ecore" xmlns:tweet="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/lexmorph/type/pos/tweet.ecore" xmlns:chunk="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/syntax/type/chunk.ecore" xmlns:type7="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/semantics/type.ecore" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:type2="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/coref/type.ecore" xmlns:toulmin="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/argumentation/types/toulmin.ecore" xmlns:morph="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/lexmorph/type/morph.ecore" xmlns:types="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/argumentation/types.ecore" xmlns:constituent="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/syntax/type/constituent.ecore" xmlns:type="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/anomaly/type.ecore" xmlns:pos="http:///de/tudarmstadt/ukp/dkpro/core/api/lexmorph/type/pos.ecore" xmi:version="2.0"><cas:NULL xmi:id="0"/><cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="Pastis wrote: &quot;But then home education isn't about learning. It's about control too. Cocooning one's children in order to isolate them from an environment in which parents are demoted from power.&quot; &#10;This is very misinformed, Pastis. Given that you appear to demand rigour in thought, eg:&#10;&quot;Most working class people would not have the social capital with which to educate their offspring. Physics, languages, Maths, Literature, History are all sophisticated subjects that require lucid explanation&quot; &#10;in order to achieve some degree of consistency, I would strongly recommend that you research your subject before you speak on it. (Also, if HE isn't about learning, then how can it be about control TOO?) &#10;Home educators neither cocoon their children in a general sense, nor do they avoid situations where their children will be subject to other forms of power. They use after school clubs, tutors in tutor groups etc, etc. &#10;And why do you assume the a priori position that teachers are necessarily superior humans who would so vastly improve the lives of children? I have recently visited a number of schools. Some teachers were delightful individuals with a wonderful approach to life and learning. Others were so AWFUL, it would have been most unpleasant to have left one's children in their care. &#10;Finally many HE parents actually don't &quot;control&quot; their children in the way you imagine. There is a large and growing community of libertarians who help their children learn consensually, non-coercively, and based on Popperian epistemology. Often mind-boggling to the uninitiated, it is both morally right and startlingly successful for those who have actually done it. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="1668" language="en" documentId="1120" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="CarlottaSF" date="29 July 2010 7:34am" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://discussion.theguardian.com/comment-permalink/6873470" topic="homeschooling" thumbsUp="6" thumbsDown="0" origId="1120" notes="" title="Home education: precious, not dangerous"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="197"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="198" end="286"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="287" end="497"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="498" end="702"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="55" sofa="1" begin="703" end="921"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="59" sofa="1" begin="922" end="1298"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="63" sofa="1" begin="1299" end="1668"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51 55 59 63"/></xmi:XMI>